                                <proc:Code>A</proc:Code>
                                <proc:Description>The Defense Threat Reduction Agency (DTRA) continues to expand its support for the Countering Weapons of Mass Destruction mission overseas.  The FY 2018 budget supports DTRA vehicles located overseas that are purchased through U.S. embassies, and provides for a vehicle program that ensures uniform serviceability to all areas.</proc:Description>
                                <proc:Justification>Funding for this budget line item provides for the procurement, maintenance, and life-cycle replacement of DTRA's non-tactical vehicles in support of missions in the U.S. and overseas.  These vehicles are operated in rocky and unpaved terrain resulting in shortened life-cycles and increased volume for maintenance.  Life-cycle requirements are based on GSA fleet management guidelines and vehicle maintenance.</proc:Justification>
